list.item:
that the Treaty for Austria shall provide that Austria shall guarantee
                            the protection of the rights of Slovene and Croat national minorities in
                            Austria;

that reparations shall not be exacted from Austria, but that
                            Yugoslavia shall have the right to seize, retain or liquidate the
                            Austrian property, rights and interests on Yugoslav territory;

that Austria shall not put any obstacles to the export of profits or
                            other income in the shape of production or freely convertible
                            currency;

that the Deputies of the Ministers shall resume their work promptly
                            for the purpose of reaching an agreement not later than September 1,
                            1949 on the draft treaty as a whole.
